               <p>2015. <persName id="def1-2015-18370814" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18370814" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18370814" type="surname" value="CRAWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18370814" type="given" value="TIMOTHY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">TIMOTHY CRAWLEY</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18370814-2015-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2015-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370814-2015-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp> for embezzlement.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1401" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1401" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1401" type="surname" value="FLOCKTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1401" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM FLOCKTON</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner was my servant—it was his duty to attend the shop during the absence of the foreman—if he has received 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Joseph Randall he has never paid it to me—it was his duty</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183708140192"></xptr>
               <p>to pay it to the foreman on his return from dinner, having a slate on which he ought to have entered it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1402" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1402" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1402" type="surname" value="RANDALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1402" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH RANDALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I went to the prosecutor's shop on the 30th of June, and paid the prisoner 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for a pint of oil.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you go a second time to the shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did on the following Monday—I pointed out the prisoner as the person who had received the money from me—there was a man who came into the shop, and I mistook him for the moment—a man dressed in a sailor's jacket—Mr. Flockton did not tell me it was impossible I could have paid him, as he was not in his employ—the prisoner came in the moment after, and I said it was him—I was asked if I could point out the person, and this other man was behind me—I had but a side view of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Now upon recollection, is it possible you may be mistaken as to the man? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I am quite positive he charged me for a pound of paint too little, and it was the cause of my knowing him—I paid the money on Friday, and went next on the Monday, and again on Tuesday by request of Mr. Flockton.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-1403" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1403" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1403" type="surname" value="MAHONEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-1403" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MAHONEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am foreman to Mr. Flockton. The prisoner attends when I am away—he did not pay me 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for paint.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What day was it that Mr. Randall called? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> On a Monday for half a pound of paint—the prisoner was in the yard—I never quarrelled with the prisoner—Randall did not see the prisoner on the second day he came, but on the third—that was Tuesday—he was taken up on Wednesday—the prisoner was accused on Tuesday—he came to work the next day, and was taken on Wednesday night.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18370814-2015-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
